-- Most Beijing Residents Expecting Yuan Appreciation, Financial News Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-12T23:48:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/most-beijing-residents-expecting-yuan-appreciation-financial-news-reports.html
More than half of Beijing’s
residents expect yuan gains in the next three months, the
Financial News reported today, citing a survey by the central
bank’s operations office.  The most recent survey found 52.6 percent of residents
expect yuan appreciation, the newspaper reported. That’s 0.6
percentage points more than the survey conducted in the last
quarter, according to the newspaper.  The Financial News newspaper is published by the People’s
Bank of China.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  